Site.Name: TMC
Site.Description: Three mile Creek downstream (ca. 10m) from a 4m high concrete dam impounding a swamp that measured approximately 6000m2. Water leaving the dam flowed over a 20m long concrete spillway before entering the stream channel. Upstream portions of the stream ran through residential areas of the City of Mobile. The north side of the sampling site was lined with large rocks and sparse vegetation, while the south side was lined with a partial canopy of tall oak trees and shrubs.
Citation: Nelder, M., Beard, C., & McCreadie, J. 2010
Host.common.name: Blackflies
Note: Spring Collections - This entry may include collections made in May 2002 and/or  March - April 2003

Site.Name: PSC
Site.Description: Pasture Creek. The upstream reaches travelled through rural and farming areas outside the city limits of Mobile. The site was located adjacent to a bridge that crossed the creek, and in an area of boulder riffle for erosion control. Pine (Pinusspp.), oak (Quercusspp.), and a thick, shrub undergrowth accompanied magnolia (Magnoliaspp.) trees on both sides of the site. The site appeared pristine and little debris was observed.
Citation: Nelder, M., Beard, C., & McCreadie, J. 2010
Host.common.name: Blackflies
Note: Summer Collections - This entry may include collections made in Jun-Aug 2002

Site.Name: HMC
Site.Description: Halls Mill Creek downstream from a bridge and in an area of boulder riffle for erosion control. Upstream areas traversed residential and rural areas of Mobile. Oak trees with a thick, undergrowth of various shrubs and herbs dominated both sides of the site. The site was moderately impacted by human activity as evidenced by occasional human-made debris in the water.
Citation: Nelder, M., Beard, C., & McCreadie, J. 2010
Host.common.name: Blackflies
Note: Spring Collections - This entry may include collections made in May 2002 and/or  March - April 2003
